INSERT INTO `share` VALUES ('118', '7', '举例论证句式1', '1. Ambition may well serve as a catalyst activating dormant potentials. …A case in point is Ms Zhang Haidi, the Chinese Helen Keller.\n\n2. Take Liu Xiang for example, who won the gold medal in the 110 meters hurdles of the 2004 Olympics, which had been the first gold medal for Asians in the Olympic track and field.\n\n【扩展】Let me cite …as an example./ A good example is that…\n\n<image src= \'http://140.143.186.35/wxci/assets/uploads/d9ca081f2805649359176e296fddce03.gif\'></image>', '2018-06-26 17:31:06', 's', null);
INSERT INTO `share` VALUES ('119', '7', '举例论证句式2', '. It means my success is your failure. If I obtain my goal, then you don’t obtain yours. It is best exemplified by a match in which individuals or teams strive against each other to obtain a goal that only one can ultimately achieve, such as a tennis or football game.\n\n4. Despite the various profits urbanization has brought to our country,many problems turn up as a result of the process: environmental deterioration, warming climate, and housing insufficiency, to name just a few.\n\n', '2018-06-26 17:31:11', 's', null);
INSERT INTO `share` VALUES ('120', '12', '真·冷门', '世界杯进行得如火如荼，开赛多日以来冷门迭出，往常空无一人的天台这段时间也因为人流过多甚至出现了需要排队的局面。\n￼\n那么“冷门”用英语该怎么表达呢？一起来了解一下吧~\n1. the unexpected winner 爆冷\n\nMexico is the unexpected winner in the match with Germany. 墨西哥爆冷击败了德国队。\n\n2. secure shock win 爆冷\n这个表达就是当年夺冠热门西班牙爆冷被瑞士队击败时BCC标题中使用的表达了，也可以表示“爆冷”之意\n\nMexico secure shock win over Germany. 墨西哥爆冷击败了德国。\n\n￼\n3. pull off an upset win 爆冷\n\nSwitzerland is not expected to beat Germany, so they are looking to pull off an upset win. 瑞士队并不被看好，所以他们希望可以爆冷。\n\n对于比赛中爆冷的，也就是实力被认为较弱不被看好的一方，也有其专有的表达\n4. underdog 比赛中不被看好者，鱼腩部队，弱者\n\nSoccer fans usually feel sympathy for the underdog. 足球迷经常会同情弱者。\n\n￼\n而比赛中被爆冷的一方，即被看好的一方或者夺冠热门，也有其表达\n5.favorite 夺冠热门\n\nThe World Cup has been won by the favorite Spain. 世界杯被夺冠热门西班牙捧起。\n\n6.shoo-in 十拿九稳者，夺冠热门\n\nSpain looked like a shoo-in to win the final. 看起来西班牙赢下决赛是十拿九稳的事。\n\n', '2018-06-26 17:32:11', 's', null);
